This article provides statements of support on the framework agreement for middle-class tax cuts and unemployment insurance. Various economists, advocacy groups, pundits, and editorial boards express their views on the deal. Overall, the statements show a mix of support and criticism for the agreement. Some economists believe that the deal will save or create jobs and boost economic activity. Pundits and editorial boards highlight the compromise and the potential for more productive years ahead. Advocacy groups commend the extension of unemployment benefits but express concerns about tax cuts for the wealthy. The article also mentions that Wall Street economists are ready to increase their economic growth forecasts for the next year in light of the tax deal.